The paper discusses a methodology combining citation network analysis and semantic analysis to study the scientific environment of a generalist journal in Geography. This methodology can be applied to other scientific environments as well. The paper does not focus on any specific computer science subfield, but the methodology and tools developed can be relevant for various subfields such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SD), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
